---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en" class="scroll-smooth">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>NFL Game Predictive Model</title>
  </head>

  <body class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
    <!-- Header Component -->
    <Header />

    <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600 text-white text-center">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-4">
          Elevator Simulation and Analysis
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-blue-100">
          A simulation of the performance of various elevators currently being proposed for a new 6-story building. 
          The simulation will provide data that will then be analyzed and used to make a recommendation to the lead architect.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!--rest of content section -->
   <section class="py-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-12">

  <!--overview section -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-10 text-center space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
      This project was a collaborative effort to design and implement an elevator simulation system in Java. 
      The goal was to model the behavior of multiple elevators, track passenger wait times, and analyze system performance to determine the most efficient elevator configuration. 
      The implementation involved building classes for core components like floors and passengers, developing a finite state machine to control elevator actions, and creating a basic GUI to visualize activity.
       The project concluded with data analysis, which showed that Elevator 3 performed the best, having the lowest average wait times and the fewest passengers who gave up.
    </p>
    
  </div>

